# Cloudflare Pages redirects.
#
# Note: same-host redirects only. Cross-host (www ↔ apex) is handled in
# functions/_middleware.ts since Pages' _redirects file cannot rewrite
# the hostname.

# Agent discovery — conventional .well-known path maps to /agents.json
# so agents following the "well-known" discovery pattern find us without
# having to read /for-agents first.
/.well-known/agents.json  /agents.json  200
/.well-known/ai.json      /agents.json  200

# Federation registry — .well-known alias for the machine-readable
# /federation.json registry. Partners' discovery tools can check the
# well-known path first before falling back to the canonical URL.
/.well-known/federation       /federation.json  200
/.well-known/federation.json  /federation.json  200

# Tezos manifest — .well-known alias. Tezos-ecosystem indexers
# (TzKT, objkt curators, fxhash ecosystem tools) following the
# well-known pattern find /tezos.json immediately.
/.well-known/tezos            /tezos.json  200
/.well-known/tezos.json       /tezos.json  200

# RFC 9727 api-catalog: spec says path is exactly /.well-known/api-catalog
# (no extension). Cloudflare Pages 404s extension-less static files, so
# keep the canonical bytes at api-catalog.json and 200-rewrite the spec
# path to it. _headers overrides Content-Type to application/linkset+json.
/.well-known/api-catalog  /.well-known/api-catalog.json  200

# RFC 9728 OAuth Protected Resource Metadata. PointCast has NO protected
# resources today; this metadata is published with empty authorization_servers
# + scopes_supported + explanatory comment so agents checking the well-known
# OAuth discovery paths get a clean "no auth required" answer instead of 404.
# OIDC discovery (/.well-known/openid-configuration) is deliberately NOT
# shipped — publishing fake issuer + endpoints would mislead agents; legitimate
# answer is "no auth." Per Mike 2026-04-20 agent-readiness audit.

# Canonical shorthand for the unified RSS feed — /rss redirects to
# /feed.xml. The legacy /rss.xml still serves the posts-only archive
# for back-compat with existing subscribers. Readers looking for "the
# PointCast RSS feed" expect /rss; this gives them /feed.xml.
/rss  /feed.xml  302

# Sprint #94 T1 (2026-04-21 22:07 PT, revised for splat syntax).
# Cloudflare Pages otherwise 308-redirects /b/N → /b/N/. Using splat
# (`*` + `:splat`) instead of named param for broadest compatibility —
# the 200 rewrite catches the request before the built-in trailing-slash
# handler kicks in, serving the directory's index.html directly.
/b/*          /b/:splat/index.html          200
/c/*          /c/:splat/index.html          200
/research/*   /research/:splat/index.html   200
